 Blessing Masakadza STAFF WRITER masakadzab@dailynews.co.zw A WOMAN from Chivhu’s Highview suburb allegedly gruesomely murdered her four children, slitting their throats with a knife before setting the house on fire after a marital dispute with her husband. The woman, Emelda Marazani, 29, allegedly downed some poison in an attempted suicide, before handing herself over to the police after being questioned by neighbours who saw smoke coming out of the house. National police spokesperson Paul Nyathi last night confirmed the incident, saying the woman took advantage of her husband’s absence after the dispute and killed the children aged one, three, five and nine. “The suspect had a marital dispute with her husband, Lameck Brande, and when the husband left for work in the morning, she locked the children in the house. “She took a rope and tied up the two older children before slitting open their throats with a knife. She went on to kill the other two children with the knife before setting the house on fire. “The suspect then drank poison which she had earlier acquired before going out. Neighbours saw some smoke coming from the house and asked her what was happening. “She said everything was in order before she handed herself over to the police,” Nyathi said. The incident comes at a time police have been raising concern over the increase in murder cases resulting from marital disputes and beer binges. googletag.cmd.push(function(){googletag.display('div-gpt-ad-1588599181508-1');}); In another incident, a man in Featherstone died after he was hit with a log on the head in a fight with his wife. “Police in Featherstone are investigating a case of murder which occurred on November 2 where a couple had a minor misunderstanding which resulted in a fight. The husband was hit with a log on the head. “He died on the way to hospital from the injuries he sustained,” police said. Sponsored Links

